# 洁癖 — Knowledge Base Neat-Freak (Skill Loader)

This rule loads the cross-platform `neat-freak` skill installed at
`~/.agents/skills/neat-freak/`. When the user's intent matches the triggers
in the frontmatter above, read the SKILL.md below and follow its instructions
verbatim before doing anything else.

## How to execute

1. Read the skill's full instructions: `@~/.agents/skills/neat-freak/SKILL.md`
2. Consult the helper references when needed:
   - `@~/.agents/skills/neat-freak/references/sync-matrix.md` — change-type → which docs to update
   - `@~/.agents/skills/neat-freak/references/agent-paths.md` — per-agent memory/config paths
3. Run the five-step flow (inventory → impact matrix → edits → self-check → summary)
   exactly as the skill specifies. Do not skip the inventory `ls` step.

## Why this rule exists (not just calling the skill directly)

Cursor's project-level `.cursor/rules/` is the reliable surface for surfacing
external skills into a Cursor session, since `~/.cursor/skills-cursor/` is
managed by Cursor's own sync and may discard manually-added entries. Keeping
the skill source at `~/.agents/skills/neat-freak/` and pointing here means a
single upgrade path for both Cursor and CLI agents.
